cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.NE 

The paper presents a computer-aided diagnosis system using convolution neural network for detecting myocardial infarction signals in ECG data. This involves transfer learning techniques to retrain pre-trained VGG-Net models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves optimization of various functions to reduce overfitting, which falls under the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of transfer learning also involves techniques from cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the application of the proposed system in urban healthcare in smart cities, which falls under the sub-category cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction). Finally, the use of neural networks for classification falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
